text: Hey guys it’s Ro!

Today I’m filming a Kitchen Haul Video,
as many of you know, I have recently

moved, and I wanted to get some stuff for
the new kitchen.

I just came back from shopping, I went to
a bunch of different stores in the area, and
I found some cute things.

So I’ve only filmed 1 Haul Video before,
and that was for my dog Cookie, so this is

actually the first Haul Video that I’ve
made, for me.

And how fitting that it is a Kitchen Haul
video, that’s something I would do.

So please go easy on me, I’m still new to
making Haul videos and I don’t really know
what I’m doing.

So without further ado, let me show you some
of the cute things I found!

When I’m shopping for kitchen stuff, one
of my first stops is always Target, because

they have adorable seasonal items and look
what I found there!
Huh!

Valentines Day is coming up and I thought
this was perfect, it is a cupcake pan, but

the cavities are shaped like little hearts,
I fell in love with it, ah-hoh-hoh-hoh-hoh!

I really like that it’s red because it really
sets it apart from my other cupcake pans.

It’s made by Wilton, you guys know I love
Wilton!
I could make heart shaped cupcakes, or heart shaped little mini cakes or brownies, there’s so many

things I could do with this so I thought,
you’re coming home with me!

Also at Target in their dollar section, like
right when you walk in there’s always seasonal

goodies there, I found these cute little heart
bowls, oh!

They’re adorable, I thought that they were
so cute, not only for Valentines Day, but
just everyday!

I like to eat granola and oatmeal in the morning,
I could be eating them out of these, they're so cute and then

look, at the bottom, they have little conversations,
this one says Love Ya, aw!

Even though these were in the dollar section,
these were actually 3 dollars.

I raided Target’s baking aisle, when I’m
on a mission for baking goods you better stay
out of my way!
#RoRaiding.

I found this really cute Silicone Jelly Roll
Pan, and it’s for making Roll cakes.

I used wax paper whenever I’m making roll
cakes, I’ve made many of them on Nerdy Nummies,

it’s the normal cake pan shape, it’s bendable,
you can roll it with the cake, I really want
to try this product because it’s so cute!

Speaking of rolling, I also found in the baking
aisle a…
Huh!
New rolling pin!
I am so excited!

I have been looking for a rolling pin that
had the same type of marble that’s in the
new kitchen.

This was perfect because it matches, it was
only like $14 and you guys, this is a little
girly and I may be taking this too far.

But it also has little light hints of pink,
just here and there.
And I went huuuuhhhh!
What!?
You?!
Are you, were you made for me!?
You’re coming with me!

Another thing that I liked about this rolling
pin is it comes with it’s own stand, I’ve

never seen that before I've never bought a rolling
pin that came with a stand.

I really like this because I can set the rolling
pin on the counter and it won’t roll away.

It can be a little decorative piece then and
I can showcase my rolling pin!

The last thing that I found at Target was
perfect for when I’m done using the rolling
pin, and made some fresh cookies.
I found…
A dinosaur cookie jar!

I have a cookie jar that I found at Target
before, it’s of a French Bulldog, but I

keep Cookie's little treats in there, so like
she has her own cookie jar, and now, I have
my own cookie jar.

For anybody who knows me, you know that I
love dinosaurs, I’m so fascinated with them,

I love Jurassic Park, and I can’t believe
that Target has a dinosaur cookie jar.

The brand that made this cookie jar is called
Threshold, they have their little logo right
here.

And they make a ton of really cute cookie
jars, they make a French Bulldog, a
little Chipmunk, a Cat.

I need to name this cookie jar, I don’t
know if it’s a him or a her.

I feel like because it’s a T-Rex, the name
Rex is too obvious, but let me know in the

comments below if you have a good dinosaur
name for this little cookie jar, because,
he needs one!
Mom!

Mom’s photo bombing my videos, ugh, she
always does this!
Cookie what is she doing!?
How do you like the new dino?
How do you like him?
Give you a kiss?

I think Cookie just wants to know if there’s
cookies in there.
Not yet Cookie…
But soon!
Next store that I went to was Sur La Table.

I feel like with that store name, the fancier
you say it, the better, I just love to say it.

I love this store because it is all about
food.

You can find a lot of baking and cooking items
and gadgets and products.

I could spend all day there, I had to limit
myself, but when I was there I found these

2 baskets, I got 2 different sizes, the larger
1 is 16-1/2 inches, and then the smaller 1
is 11-3/4 inches.

These are the Sur La Table Madeline basket
with liner, and these are perfect for me and

my new space because I now have fruit trees,
and I’ve got to harvest the fruit multiple
times a year.

I like these for many reasons, I fell in love
with them.

1 because they’re lightweight, they’re
made out of a lightweight metal, so that when

you’re carrying around the fruit the only
weight that you’re holding is from the fruit,

the lemons, the limes, the tangerines, and
not the weight of the basket.

And 2, it’s got a little fabric liner, it’s
adorable, and when it gets dirty from catching

all the leaves and the dirt from the fruit,
you can take it off and wash it.

3 they added some cute design detail at the
bottom, they wove a little bit of wood and
painted it to be the same color of the metal.
This is a good looking fruit picking basket.

When life gives you a lemon tree, you gotta
get a fruit picking basket to harvest all
of them.
A-ha-ha-ha-ha-ha-ha-ha!

Next item is the thing that I splurged on
for this haul, I got a pasta maker, the Atlas 150.
I’m so excited to own one of these for myself.

My mom has had one of these for decades and
decades, and one of the traditions in our family

is to make handmade pasta with this machine,
every year for christmas.

You guys may have seen it on my SnapChat,
I posted a bunch of videos of us making handmade

pasta and I really wanted to continue those
traditions.

So, I feel so adult, I have my very first
pasta maker of my own.

And, I’ll put a little video over here too, my
Mom’s poor pasta maker has been through

a lot, it’s lost its clamp and pieces, and
we’ve tried to MacGyver it, but, it takes
3 people to operate.

There’s like 1 person holding down the thing,
1 holding down the connecting.

It takes teamwork, it’s kind of funny, But now,
we have 1 that 1 person can operate!

To make pasta, you feed the dough through
and it flattens it out evenly.

You can feed it through multiple times to
get your desired flat-ness of noodle, and

the second thing that it does is it will cut
your pasta, so you can make fettuccine, lasagna,
spaghetti, whatever you’d like.
So this one was a winner-winner, pasta dinner!

The next thing that I found was a little bit
random because I found it at Nordstrom Rack,

and I know what you’re thinking, Nordstrom
Rack!?
That’s like clothes and shoes and stuff.

But, they have a very small home section,
which I like to check up out because…
Huh, I found these, little cute copper mugs!

These mugs have become pretty popular this
year, I saw them at every store that I went

to, a lot of my friends and family are drinking
the popular drink Moscow Mules out of these.

And I have a really yummy recipe if you guys
are interested, I’ll put a link down below.

These mugs are a little bit more on the expensive
side, so I held off on until buying them until

I found some on sale, because they are made
of copper, they’re really good insulators,

they keep your drink cold, and for a lot of
the drinks that are served in these mugs,

you fill it all the way to the top with ice,
add your ingredients, a little splash of lime,

and your drink stays cold the whole time you’re
sipping on it.

They’re usually about $20 a mug, but these
were on sale at Nordstrom Rack for $12 a mug!

Next stop was Crate & Barrel, I love Crate
& Barrel, I could probably spend an entire
day there, or I could live there.

Actually guys, that’s my new house, we’re
gonna do a house tour and I’m just running
around Crate & Barrel!
I found these!

You guys they’re stainless steel measuring
spoons and cups, but they’re magnetic!
So you can really gently just pull them apart.

This brand was OXO Good Grips, and I have
some storage containers by them, I really
liked them so I thought, let’s try ‘em!

Speaking of storage, when I was at Crate & Barrel
I found these glass storage containers.

I had been looking for some glass ones for
a long time and these were the perfect size.

I got a medium sized one with 2 small ones
in there, and then a larger 3 piece set if
I have larger sized leftovers.

I really wanted to get some glass containers
for a few reasons.

1, is because they’re microwaveable, you want to make
sure that they’re microwave safe.

If I have some leftovers in here I can just
pop off the top, put it in the microwave,

reheat it, and then eat it right out of the
container.

And, 2nd reason, I wanted something that was
really durable and high quality, and that
would last me a bunch of years.

Another thing that I found was very simple,
it’s a paper towel holder.

But I loved it because it’s made out of
marble, so it matches the materials in my new
kitchen, and it’s heavy.

Because it’s made of marble, it has a lot
of weight, and when I put the paper towel

roll on it and I pull a towel, it doesn’t
move around.

My old one would move along with me and I’d
have to be like, no!
No! Stop!

I never thought I would get this excited about
a paper towel holder…
But I am!
Tee-hee-hee!

The last thing that I found from Crate & Barrel
were these martini glasses, I got 4 of them,

and I realized, over the holidays when we
had friends and family over, we had a bunch

of fresh lemons from my lemon tree and we
were making everything lemon.

Fresh Lemonade, Lemon Meringue Pies, Lemon
Bars, Lemon Drops.

And when we were making Lemon Drops, I realized
that I don’t have any martini glasses, I

only had wine glasses, and I thought, I need
some entertainment ware!

I feel like I could have James Bond over,
and he would approve.
Oh thanks, 00-Ro!

Last store I stopped at was Bed Bath & Beyond,
BB&B!

And I found an electric citrus juicer, I was
looking for 1 of these, because I have a little

manual 1, which I love to use if I’m just
making a small cup of orange juice, or a little
treat for myself or friends.

But now that I have citrus trees, I have a
lot more citrus to handle, so I needed to
get something electric, and I found this one.

This one is by Cuisinart, and I really liked
it because it has a pulp control feature,

on my manual one, I didn’t have any choices,
but on this one, you can control.

There’s three settings, low, medium, or
super pulp.

Depending on what recipe you’re gonna make,
whether it’s lemon bars, or you just want

some fresh juice, you can control how much
pulp you’re getting.

I see a lot of yummy citrus recipes in the
future.

Alright, that is everything, that does it
for my kitchen haul video.

I’ll be putting links to everything that
I talked about, if it has a link, down below

in the description box, so if you want to
check them out, you can do that down there.

I hope you guys enjoyed this video, this was
my first Kitchen Haul Video, and I loved making it.

Also if have any other ideas of any other
types of videos you’d like to see, let me
know in the comments below.
Alright, thanks again, bye-bye!
